Also forgot to mention, its a single animal project
and i tried to write track_method: None 
still no solution

Hi @KazanovI, could you show us the content of the folder `C:\Users\itaykaza\Desktop\DLC\RAW videos\10_jan_2022`? For a single-animal project, there should be a file named `Pupil_22éðå10_104644.000DLC_resnet50_pupillometryDec22shuffle1_1030000.h5`, although I'm not sure whether the special characters may be causing trouble.

so, i changed the names of the videos to other generic name and IT WORKED! 
thank you very much for the quick response !

### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

hey,

I installed DLC using the guidelines in your documentation on a workstation. I Copied an existing neural network to a network drive and used it to analyze a mouse tracking video, that is local on the workstation. The analysis works and creates a .csv, but I'm missing the .h5 file to create a labeled video. 
I do the same process steps, using the GUI, on an other computer and the outcome is fine, so I guess my environment and/or installation is wrong. 


Best
Laurenz

Win10

### DeepLabCut version

DLC version 2.2.0.3, downloaded out of the installation guide from the documentation.

A similar case was reported here: https://github.com/DeepLabCut/DeepLabCut/issues/1635
but the solution did not fit for me. 

I also got the Error: Failed to launch ptxas, as described in the Issue above, but the solution helped to solve that.
